What is MinEd? (Pronounce "min-ed")

Mined is a powerful text editor with a comprehensive and easy-to-use 
user interface and fast, small-footprint behaviour.

For an overview of major features and highlights, see http://towo.net/mined/

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The DOS version of mined should be installed in a binary directory in 
your DOS search path (PATH variable).
In a command prompt, type
	MINED options files
to invoke mined in the DOS console.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Info: The DOS version of mined was built with djgpp.
It supports console codepages on MSDOS and FreeDOS.

